<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,437,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Etymology</emphasis>
: This species is named for Dr. R. R. Askew, who has contributed substantially to our knowledge of European 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1820" box="[784,943,1204,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pteromalidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1870]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,403,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Biology</emphasis>
: Unknown; like other species from this genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[969,1086,1244,1269]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[969,1086,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1095,1159,1244,1270]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is probably a parasitoid of a certain species of 
<taxonomicName box="[648,736,1284,1310]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
(in this case probably a species of moderate size). All the individuals were swept on steppe vegetation at Valea lui David Natural Reserve. More than 500 species of angiosperms were identified here, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[1095,1191,1364,1390]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
being the dominant species (
<bibRefCitation author="Mititelu, D. &amp; Motiu, T. &amp; TeSu, C. &amp; Vitalariu, C." box="[482,714,1404,1430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" pagination="81 - 100" refId="ref7555" refString="Mititelu, D., Motiu, T., D a sc a lescu, D., TeSu, C., Vitalariu, C. (1969) Flora Si vegetatia pajiStilor &quot; Valea lui David &quot; IaSi. Studii S i Comunic a ri, Muzeul de S tiin t ele Naturii Bac a u, 81 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1969">Mititelu &amp; al. 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1325,284,1870]" lastBlockId="8.[264,1323,284,510]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,671,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[433,671,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">Halticoptera askewi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[679,743,1444,1470]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the group of species with the median area of propodeum distinctly reticulated, together with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Curtis)" baseAuthorityName="Curtis" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[977,1272,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smaragdina">
<emphasis box="[977,1162,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. smaragdina</emphasis>
(Curtis)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dalman)" baseAuthorityName="Dalman" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. patellana</emphasis>
(Dalman)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[508,744,1524,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[508,633,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. collaris</emphasis>
(Walker)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Graham. The" authorityName="Graham. The" authorityYear="1972" box="[800,1122,1524,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatula">
<emphasis box="[800,961,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. elongatula</emphasis>
Graham. The
</taxonomicName>
female and male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[296,412,1564,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[296,412,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[420,482,1564,1590]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
would run in Graham’s key (1969) as far as couplet 3 and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dalman)" baseAuthorityName="Dalman" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellana">
<emphasis box="[1176,1322,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">H. patellana</emphasis>
(Dalman)
</taxonomicName>
, on account of its distinctly reticulated propodeum and, in the case of the male, also on account of its small maxillary stipites. From both sexes of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dalman" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[1097,1207,1644,1669]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellana">
<emphasis box="[1097,1207,1644,1669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">patellana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this new species differs mainly in having a very transverse petiole, a larger body size and some other characteristic features, which are mentioned below. Some of the characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[1243,1322,1724,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1243,1322,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[264,327,1764,1790]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are rather uncommon for most of the species in the genus: an almost sessile gaster, OOL much longer than POL, a very distinct frenal groove, and the bottom edge of the toruli slightly above lower edge of eyes. The presence of these characters could question the generic placement of this species. However, other characters i.e. the rounded collar of the pronotum, the slightly asymmetric bidentate margin of the clypeus, the antennal formula, the postmarginal vein which is shorter than the marginal vein and the enlarged male maxillary palpi, do indicate that 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitroiu, 2005" authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[708,788,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[708,788,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[795,857,404,430]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1811" box="[1068,1218,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1218,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Halticoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I do not think it is appropriate to create a new subgenus for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mitroiu" authorityYear="2005" box="[940,1020,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Halticoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askewi">
<emphasis box="[940,1020,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">askewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
before examining more material, especially from the Central and East Palearctic.
</paragraph>
